 this day. Also, July 7th is the birthday of
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 the
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 God of Studying "Kuei Shin."
}
\par \pard\plain \s21\ql\nowidctlpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\aspalpha\sb0\sa0\ltrpar\cf0\dbch\af6\langfe2052\dbch\af5\afs20\alang1081\loch\f5\fs20\lang1033{\rtlch \ltrch \~}

{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
The
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 Ghost Festival is on July 15th,
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 which day
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 is the birthday of Diguan
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
, the
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 God in charge of hell. From July 1st to 30th is what we
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 call
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 the ghost month and also the month when people start "Pu Do". Some places
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 will perform
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 this ceremony on the 15th, and others
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 will
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 do it on the 20th. Pu Do has two different
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 explanations. One of these comes
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 from Buddhism,
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 where it involves asking
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 people
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 to
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 be nice to their parents
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
. There, Pu Do
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 is also called
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 the
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 "Meng Lan Pen Festival
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
," a reference to
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 the story of "Mu Lian
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 rescuing
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 her mother from hell." On this day, many Buddhists
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 will
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 hire many monks
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 to chant blessings for
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 their parents who
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 have
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 passed away. In
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 Taoism,
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 Pu Do
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 involves feeding
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 the starved ghosts and
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 burning
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 paper money for them to use in the other world. There are many different activities during
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 the
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 Ghost Festival. Pu Do is divided into two different types
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
, characterized as
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 public
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 or
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 private. Private Pu Do is held by companies or individuals, and the public
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 type is carried out
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 by temples
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
. The
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 biggest event called "Yi Ming Pu Do" on July 20th
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 is of this second sort.
}
\par \pard\plain \s21\ql\nowidctlpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\aspalpha\sb0\sa0\ltrpar\cf0\dbch\af6\langfe2052\dbch\af5\afs20\alang1081\loch\f5\fs20\lang1033{\rtlch \ltrch \~}

{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
The Mid-Autumn Festival
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 is on August 15th. This festival
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 comes
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 from the well-known folk stories of Chang Er escaping to the moon,
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 the Rabbit
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 pounding medicine and Wu Gang chopping down the Cinnamon
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 Tree. August 15th
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 is also the birthday of Bogung. People usually worship Bogung in the daytime and worship the moon
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 in the evening.
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 When worshiping the moon,
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 people
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 also
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 pay their respects
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 to Chang Er
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
,
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 who is called Goddess Tai Yin
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 too.
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 On August 15th, we also need to eat moon cakes
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
. But
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 why?
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 This comes
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 from the story
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 of
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 when Liu Bo Wen tried to overthrow the Yuan Dynasty; he put notes in
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 moon
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 cakes for passing
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 messages.
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 Hence, people started to eat moon cakes in order to
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 remember
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 his great courage.
}
\par \pard\plain \s21\ql\nowidctlpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\aspalpha\sb0\sa0\ltrpar\cf0\dbch\af6\langfe2052\dbch\af5\afs20\alang1081\loch\f5\fs20\lang1033{\rtlch \ltrch \~}

{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
September 9th is
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 the
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 Chung Yeung Festival and it is
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 a
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 day to pay our
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 respects
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 to the elderly. We all know to climb mountains on that day
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
. But
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 why?
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 This comes
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 from a rustic story
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 about
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 Huan Jing
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
, who
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 wanted to be immortal so he found a master to teach him some tricks. One day, his master asked him to
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 take
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 his
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 family
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 and escape to
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 the
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 mountain on Sept. 9th. The master also asked him to
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 take
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 some cakes and Chrysanthemum wine for the trip. When he came home
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 on
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 the evening of
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 the
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 9th, he found out all his animals
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 had
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 died so he finally realized that the master was trying to save
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 his and his family\uc2 \u8217\'81\'66s lives. Thereafter
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
, people started to climb
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 mountains
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
, drink Chrysanthemum wine and eat Chung Yeung cake to remember this story. However, the day has changed to become
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 one
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 to pay our
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 respects to the elderly
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 these
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 days. But
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 the traditional activity
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 is still a great
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 way
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 to show our love to
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 our
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 parents and grandparents.
}
\par \pard\plain \s21\ql\nowidctlpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\aspalpha\sb0\sa0\ltrpar\cf0\dbch\af6\langfe2052\dbch\af5\afs20\alang1081\loch\f5\fs20\lang1033{\rtlch \ltrch \~}

{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 After
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 the
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 Chung Yeung Festival, it is the time of
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 the
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 winter solstice.
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 The winter solstice
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 occurs on
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 the shortest
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 day
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 and the longest night
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 of the
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 year. Hakka people call it
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 the
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 Winter Festival
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 and it
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 is also the birthday of cows. We 
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 will
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 make boiled glutinous rice balls and wrap
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 them with leaves. This is
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 a
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 treat for cows
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
, thanking them for
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 their hard work
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 over
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 the
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 previous
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 few years. People believe all objects have spirits attached
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 to
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 them, so they will stick the rice balls on the table, on the well and even on
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 hen houses. You could say that
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 the Winter Festival
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 is the birthday of every object on earth. In
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 ancient
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 times, people used to make all kinds of contracts
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 at
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 this time and
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 follow
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 them after New Year.   
}
\par \pard\plain \s21\ql\nowidctlpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\aspalpha\sb0\sa0\ltrpar\cf0\dbch\af6\langfe2052\dbch\af5\afs20\alang1081\loch\f5\fs20\lang1033{\rtlch \ltrch \~}

{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
And later, it is the day to send off
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 the
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 Gods
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 on
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 December 23
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
rd
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 or 24th.
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 According to
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 legend, the God of Stove was sent to supervise everyone\uc2 \u8217\'81\'66s behavior and record
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 it
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 in a book.
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 By
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 December 24th, he would report the
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 findings
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 to Tian Gung. To prevent him saying too
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 many
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 bad
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 things
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 to Tian Gung, people would
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 pay
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 him
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 tribute
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
, such as melon candy or maltose, hoping he could say good things only.
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 Besides
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 candy,
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 people would
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 also burn paper horses for him to hurry
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 him
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 up
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 on
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 the trip to
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 the
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 sky. However, this kind of ritual has already disappeared now.
}
\par \pard\plain \s21\ql\nowidctlpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\aspalpha\sb0\sa0\ltrpar\cf0\dbch\af6\langfe2052\dbch\af5\afs20\alang1081\loch\f5\fs20\lang1033{\rtlch \ltrch \~}

{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Finally, it is New Year\uc2 \u8217\'81\'66s Eve
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
,
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 which is also
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 Hakka
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 New Year. During their New Year, they will butcher chickens
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 and
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 ducks to worship
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 God
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
. Also, they
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 will
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 post spring couplets and clean the incense furnace. Because all the Gods are going back to the sky,
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 this won\uc2 \u8217\'81\'66t offend
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 them. In
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 olden
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 times,
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 an
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 adopted daughter could get married on this day.
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 Besides
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 butchering animals for
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 offerings
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
, people used to make all
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 New Year\uc2 \u8217\'81\'66s
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 dishes on
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 this day.
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 At night, children
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 will
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 come back home and
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 eat a
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 family feast together.
