 would
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 need to worship Goddess Jou Sheng and Goddess Guanyin right away for
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 the sake of
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 the health of their new baby.
}
\par \pard\plain \s21\ql\nowidctlpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\aspalpha\sb0\sa0\ltrpar\cf0\dbch\af6\langfe2052\dbch\af5\afs20\alang1081\loch\f5\fs20\lang1033{\rtlch \ltrch \~}

{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
When having the baby, they need to
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 do
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 "Duan Chi" and get "Bau Yi." But where should
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 they
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 place
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 the
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 Bau Yi? Some people believe if having a boy, it should be put under the door and if having a girl, it should be put in the garden. Placing it under the door means the boy will be smart, and placing it in the garden means the girl will have good fortune. So Hakka people would say the location of
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 the
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 Bau Yi is also the place where you were born.
}
\par \pard\plain \s21\ql\nowidctlpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\aspalpha\sb0\sa0\ltrpar\cf0\dbch\af6\langfe2052\dbch\af5\afs20\alang1081\loch\f5\fs20\lang1033{\rtlch \ltrch \~}

{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
After three days, the newborn baby would
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 be given
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 a bath. Some people
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 would soak
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 Longan leaves, and some would
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 soak
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 osmanthus or banyan branches
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 in
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 the water. Also, a stone and some coins would be placed in the water
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 to bless
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 the baby with courage and health. In addition,
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 in
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 Hakka
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 custom,
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 people would do
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 "Shih
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 Er Chau" or "Shih San Chau" which means to inform the
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 mother\uc2 \u8217\'81\'66s parents of
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 the good news. If having a boy, the
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 maternal grandmother
