 is rather different.
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 Some people would
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 call
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 them "Chi Tou" or "Chu Tou" (Tzou Yi). It is different in some Hakka areas. For example, in Hsinchu, if people celebrate their Chu Tou
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 at
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 71, 61 and 51
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
, it
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 means both wife and husband are still alive. If
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 it is
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 Chi Tou, it means one of them has passed away.
}
\par \pard\plain \s21\ql\nowidctlpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\aspalpha\sb0\sa0\ltrpar\cf0\dbch\af6\langfe2052\dbch\af5\afs20\alang1081\loch\f5\fs20\lang1033{\rtlch \ltrch \~}

{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
People would make birthday noodles and turtle rice cake for their
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 birthdays. The turtle
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 symbolizes long life and prosperity. We would eat eggs, and pig feet for good luck as well. Long life is the main wish
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 of
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 people
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 usually,
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 and birthday
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 celebrations are
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 one of the customs of our society.
}
\par \pard\plain \s21\ql\nowidctlpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\aspalpha\sb0\sa0\ltrpar\cf0\dbch\af6\langfe2052\dbch\af5\afs20\alang1081\loch\f5\fs20\lang1033{\rtlch \ltrch \~}

{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Next, it is the ritual of
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 the
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 funeral. The start point
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 for humans
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 is the day when we were born, and the ending of life is death. In order to pay
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 respects
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 to our parents and express our grief,
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 we
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 have these rituals.
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 A
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 funeral is usually sad, but we would hope to handle it peacefully and respectfully. 
}
\par \pard\plain \s21\ql\nowidctlpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\aspalpha\sb0\sa0\ltrpar\cf0\dbch\af6\langfe2052\dbch\af5\afs20\alang1081\loch\f5\fs20\lang1033{\rtlch \ltrch \~}

{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
If a man
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 passes
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 away, it
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 is said,
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 "He rests peacefully
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
--
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Shou Jung Cheng Chin." If it
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 is
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 a woman, it
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 is said,
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 "Shou Jung Nei Chin" with
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 a
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 similar meaning. After death,
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 the
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 family
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 would put
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 a
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 shroud on the deceased and move the body to the "Ting Shia
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
--
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
The living room." Some would be moved
