 the deceased to use in the other world.
}
\par \pard\plain \s21\ql\nowidctlpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\aspalpha\sb0\sa0\ltrpar\cf0\dbch\af6\langfe2052\dbch\af5\afs20\alang1081\loch\f5\fs20\lang1033{\rtlch \ltrch \~}

{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
The family
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 would guard the body to not let any animals such as cats or rats
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 climb over it
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
. Monks would be invited again to make sure the deceased can rest in peace. During
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 the funeral, the family
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 would release
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 an
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 obituary.
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 On
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 the door would
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 be posted
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 a white cloth with the words "Yan Chih" on it if it was a father
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 who
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 passed away and "Chr Chih" if it was a mother. The day to do good deeds and the time to bury
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 the body would need
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 to be
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 planned
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 carefully.
}
\par \pard\plain \s21\ql\nowidctlpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\aspalpha\sb0\sa0\ltrpar\cf0\dbch\af6\langfe2052\dbch\af5\afs20\alang1081\loch\f5\fs20\lang1033{\rtlch \ltrch \~}

{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
There are two kinds of
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 good deed; one
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 kind
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 is
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 Taoist,
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 and one is
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 Buddhist.
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 The categories
