 performed.
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 All the above are the rituals for
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 funerals.
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 However, many people choose cremation instead of interment now, so these rituals can be skipped. Also, in order to save some
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 trouble,
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 Chi will be done after burying the body. An Lin and Chu Lin will be done together later. Nowadays, the rituals for
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 funerals
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 are simplified
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
, skipping
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 many complicated processes.
}
\par \pard\plain \s21\ql\nowidctlpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\aspalpha\sb0\sa0\ltrpar\cf0\dbch\af6\langfe2052\dbch\af5\afs20\alang1081\loch\f5\fs20\lang1033{\rtlch \ltrch \~}

{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Goal of lesson: After
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 this
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 lesson, you will be able to: 1. Understand the origin of the religion of Yi Ming. 2. Realize
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 the meaning of
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 the worship activities of
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 the
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 Yi Ming Festival.
}
\par \pard\plain \s21\ql\nowidctlpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\aspalpha\sb0\sa0\ltrpar\cf0\dbch\af6\langfe2052\dbch\af5\afs20\alang1081\loch\f5\fs20\lang1033{\rtlch \ltrch \~}

{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
There are more than 130 Yi Ming temples in Hakka villages with numerous followers.  Yi Ming Ye was a great man who
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 sacrificed his life
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 to protect his hometown. Hence, people respect him as a God and worship him yearly.
}
\par \pard\plain \s21\ql\nowidctlpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\aspalpha\sb0\sa0\ltrpar\cf0\dbch\af6\langfe2052\dbch\af5\afs20\alang1081\loch\f5\fs20\lang1033{\rtlch \ltrch \~}

{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
The worship
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 of
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 Yi Ming Ye is a special
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 cultural tradition
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 among
}{\cf2\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 the
}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 Hakka. The biggest temple is in Sinpu Fangliao, Hsinchu County. It is called "Bao Jung" Yi Ming temple because the temple has
